name: CALAVERITA DE TINTA
description:
Technique: Ink on paper.
Calaberita de Tinta" is a representation of a sugar skull. The sugar skull is an object that is placed in a ritual display during the annual and traditionally mexican "Día de Muertos" celebration.
These skulls play a large role in "Dia de Muertos" and it’s a way for people to honor their dead.
